				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">There is always an excuse.
<br />

<br />
Freedom of speech is a major security risk.  Someone may incite a riot
<br />
Freedom of the press is a major security risk.  They may print damaging state secrets.
<br />
Freedom of assembly is a security is a major security risk.  A large violent mob could do terrible harm.
<br />
The right to bear arms is a major security risk.  Someone with a gun could shoot you.
<br />
Search warrants are a major security risk.  In the time it takes to go to a judge and explain the need evidence could be destroyed.
<br />
Speedy public trials are a major security risk.  They interrupt interrogations and allow criminals to pass messages to their accomplices.
<br />
A ban on cruel and unusual punishment is a major security risk.  Torture is the only way to get some people to talk, and we must make an example of some people, or others will be tempted to do bad things.
<br />
States rights are a major security risk.  One state may permit something which is illegal in another state and a person may cross state lines to commit a crime.
<br />

<br />
Yes  every freedom that made America a great nation is a major security risk.   We would all be much safer if the government had microphones in all our houses to protect us from crime.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
