				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'm saddened by the treatment of the Iraqi prisoners.  I'm horrified by prospects of further occupation and the repurcussions it will have for our armed forces and our nation.  I'm still glad I saw the pictures.  I clearly have a civilian perspective on things.  I think that national security must be protected.  I can, however, in no way see how humane treatment of prisoners falls under that blanket.  Our treatment of Iraqi resistance elements may stand contrary to immediate military goals.  Not treating them humanely, however, makes us scorned hypocrites in the eyes of the world, especially in the Middle East.
<br />

