			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">The press certainly has its flaws, but preventing this sort of thing is why the protection of free speech and the press are as crucial to the world as they are.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I don't think you are getting the point.
<br />

<br />
This isn't about censoring the press. It is about the press being responsible with information they have. 
<br />

<br />
You seem totally unable to grasp the fact that the release of the photos put people lives in danger. Why can you not grasp that. Sure Nick Berg probably would have met the same fate as Dan Pearl regardless and I did step a bit far onto that slipperly slope of logic as Dd pointed out. 
<br />

<br />
The presses wreckless disregard for the environment they created by releasing the photos int he pursuit of the almighty dollar via sensational news reporting can only lead to more and more insurgent activity in Iraq. Common sense would have told the editors this.
<br />

<br />
Common sense would also tell the person who released the photos to them the same thing and that the media would do exactly what they did.
<br />

<br />
Your own political leanings are exactly why you take the opposite stance. I don't give two shits who is in office in this situation and never brought it up and I dont' think Rsak did either. You seem to know our minds though since you have said more than once that we would be blaming the Pres if he were a Demo. No I would not. I would blame the fucking wreckless idiot who put my comrades in danger. 
<br />

<br />
I may just stop arguing this point with you since you are too thick to get that your moral decision to release information to the public that may cause the deaths of many is somehow the right thing to do. Use the system, if the system does not work then use the media. Not a hard concept to grasp. Too bad there is so much money in selling your story to the media.
<br />

<br />
We have freedom of speech in this country for some very good reasons. The ability to release information without regard to the potential harm it may cause is not one of them. I don't really know how explain to you my viewpoint any better. 
<br />

<br />
Regardless of the informations content our media must wiegh the potential cost of disclosure to innocent parties. How could one not see the potential dangers in releasing this information would pose to our soldiers and civilian workers in Iraq. It is idiotic, wreckless and potentially illegal. American's are held accountable for the results of their actions, except the media (well and sometimes the CIC apparently). Maybe it is time we held them accountable.
<br />

<br />
Tora</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
